UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022199601001106
KW  - Grey markets
KW  - Parallel imports
AB  - This paper demonstrates that, when countries individually choose whether or not to prohibit parallel imports, a global Nash equilibrium involves the permitting of parallel importing into all relevant foreign markets i.e. global uniform pricing. This result is sensitive in a straightforward way to the tariff-setting powers of countries and to the specification of a government’s objective function (i.e. political economy considerations). We also show that when countries can prevent ‘parallel exports’ then any Nash equilibrium involves global price discrimination.
